name: Ankita Classic Warkhand Road

reviews.review_text: The prawns in the starters were enjoyable, but unfortunately, the mix fried rice contained artificial prawns instead of real ones, which was disappointing. The overall experience was below average as the hospitality was not up to the mark. While some dishes were decent, the food quality overall left room for improvement.

A Must-Visit Gem on Warkhand Road – Ankita Classic!

While traveling from Goa towards Maharashtra, we stumbled upon Ankita Classic on Warkhand Road, and it turned out to be the highlight of our journey! From the moment we stepped in, it was a delightful experience, thanks to the warm hospitality of Host Rahul Dalvi, who made us feel right at home.

The seafood is nothing short of awesome – fresh, flavorful, and perfectly cooked! The portions were generous, and the pricing was unbelievably reasonable for the quality and quantity we received.

The interiors are simply outstanding – a visual treat! It’s rare to find such a beautifully designed space along the highway. With a seating capacity of over 350 people, it’s perfect for large gatherings, yet cozy enough for a family meal.

Parking is often a challenge on long road trips, but not here – there’s ample parking space to accommodate vehicles of all sizes.

If you’re a seafood lover and appreciate great ambiance, Ankita Classic is a must-visit. It’s more than just a restaurant; it’s an experience you’ll cherish! Don’t miss this gem if you’re traveling in the area.

I visited this place twice and it was fantastic. Large parking space, good ambience, staffs behaviour was good all are cooperative. I tasted 10 different types of fishes here and all were good in taste. Actually I ordered starters those were good in taste and later ordered thali. Thali was good but not able to finish full thali because it was too big. So I would suggest if you order starters then surely go for small thali and share big thali because lots of food will waste later. So, I would suggest you should visit this place once if you are seafood lover and it is affordable not too costly.

### Ankita Classic: A Culinary Jewel on Warkhand Road

Nestled along Warkhand Road in Naval Base Verem, **Ankita Classic** boasts an impressive rating of **4.5** stars, with **3,600** reviews attesting to its popularity. This charming restaurant is celebrated primarily for its **seafood**, including standout dishes like **fish thali** and **kingfish**, alongside enticing options such as **squids**. With such enthusiastic feedback from customers, it stands out as a destination worth seeking out.

### Ambiance & Design

Upon entering Ankita Classic, guests are greeted by a beautifully designed interior, described by many as a **visual treat**. The spacious venue can accommodate over **350 diners**, making it ideal for large gatherings while maintaining a cozy atmosphere for family meals. Reviews highlighted the **warm hospitality** provided by staff, particularly the commendable service from host **Rahul Dalvi**. Lighting is soft and inviting, creating a welcoming environment that complements the artistic décor depicted in customer images. 

### Menu & Culinary Experience

Ankita Classic is a haven for seafood aficionados. Diners rave about the **freshness** and **flavor** of the dishes. Signature offerings include a variety of **fish types** expertly prepared and presented. Customers often rave about the **starters** and the **generously-sized thalis**, which can be quite the feast—so much so that guests are advised to share the larger portions to avoid wastage. The combination of quality, taste, and **affordable** pricing makes dining here a satisfying experience.

However, not every aspect has been flawless. Some reviews mentioned disappointment with certain dishes, such as artificial ingredients in the **mixed fried rice**, indicating potential inconsistencies in food quality. Nevertheless, many patrons still consider this establishment a must-visit for its delectable seafood.

### Customer Experience & Service

Customer service at Ankita Classic has been noted for its **efficiency** and **friendliness**. The staff is described as cooperative and accommodating, providing guests with a fulfilling dining experience. Ample parking is another boon for those on long road trips, allowing for straightforward access to this culinary spot without the usual travel frustrations.

### Popularity & Reviews

The buzz surrounding Ankita Classic extends beyond word-of-mouth. Its **social media presence** showcases satisfied diners enthusiastically sharing their plates, reflecting the restaurant’s vibrant atmosphere and the quality of the culinary offerings. The blend of **great food**, **friendly service**, and an **inviting ambiance** has made it a favorite among travelers and locals alike.

### Utilizing Visual Content

Customer-provided photos highlight the restaurant’s **scenic interiors**, adorned with tasteful decorations that create a relaxed yet engaging dining atmosphere. Visuals of beautifully plated seafood dishes reinforce the restaurant's reputation for quality and presentation, while snapshots of satisfied diners enjoying their meals encapsulate the essence of a memorable dining experience.

In conclusion, **Ankita Classic** on Warkhand Road is more than just a restaurant; it is an **experience** that combines flavorful seafood with warm hospitality in a delightful setting. Whether you are a seafood lover or simply looking for a charming place to dine, this gem is well worth the visit.
